import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    ages = data['age']
    plt.hist(ages, bins=10, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(ages.mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean Age: {ages.mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['height'], vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, 
               labels=['Height'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average height of people in the dataset?')
    ax.axvline(data['height'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', 
               label=f'Mean: {data["height"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['age'], data['height'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between age and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(name_counts.index, name_counts.values)
    plt.title('What are the most common names in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    steve_data = data[data['name'] == 'Steve']
    plt.hist(steve_data['age'], bins=10, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=steve_data['age'].mean(), color='red', label='mean age: {:.2f}'.format(steve_data['age'].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title("What is the age distribution of people with the name 'Steve' in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
